Loop
A structure that allows repeating a block of code multiple times.

Infinite Loop
A loop that runs endlessly because its terminating condition is never met.

Index
The position of an element in a sequence, starting from 0.

Slicing
Extracting a portion of a sequence by specifying a start, stop, and step.

Shallow Copy
A copy of a collection object that only copies the references to the objects within the collection.

Deep Copy
A copy of a collection object that recursively copies all objects within the collection.

List Comprehension
A concise way to create lists using a single line of code.

Function
A block of reusable code that performs a specific task.

Recursion
A function that calls itself in order to solve a problem.

String Concatenation
Combining two or more strings into a single string.